<ets>meten</ets>, G. <ets>messen</ets>, OHG. <ets>mezzan</ets>, Icel.
<ets>meta</ets>, Sw. <ets>m⟦aum⟧ta</ets>, Goth. <ets>mitan</ets>, L.
<ets>modus</ets> measure, moderation, <ets>modius</ets> a corn measure,
Gr. <?/ to rule, <?/ a corn measure, and ultimately from the same root
as E. <ets>measure</ets>, L. <ets>metiri</ets> to measure; cf. Skr.
<ets>m⟦amac⟧</ets> to measure. ⟦root⟧99. Cf. <er>Measure</er>,
<er>Meet</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, <er>Mode</er>.]</ety> <def>To find the
quantity, dimensions, or capacity of, by any rule or standard; to
measure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

